embly and cannot be separated. This procedure covers the removal of the oil and coolant pump assembly. ","Perform the following operations:","Seat - Removal","Battery - Removal","Radiator - Removal","Exhaust System - Removal","Drain the engine oil (see ","Oil and Oil Filter Change",")","Sump - Removal","Clutch - Removal","Make sure that the engine is securely mounted in an engine stand or properly supported when it is removed from the motorcycle.","If the engine is not correctly supported, it can fall.","Failure to follow the advice above could result in damage to property or serious injury.","Remove and discard the two fixings and remove the oil transfer pipe.","Remove and discard the two O-ring seals. ","Oil transfer pipe","Fixings","Remove and discard the two fixings and remove the oil pick-up.","Remove and discard the O-ring seal.","Oil pick-up","Fixings","Remove and discard the bolt that attaches the coolant outlet pipe to the crankcase and withdraw the pipe.","Remove and discard the O-rings from the elbow.","Coolant outlet pipe","Fixing","Remove and discard the bolt that attaches the coolant inlet elbow to the crankcase and remove the elbow.","Remove and discard the O-ring from the elbow.","Coolant inlet pipe","Fixing","Remove the fixings that attach the drive chain guide to the crankcase and remove the guide.","Oil pump drive chain guide (engine shown inverted)","Fixings","Slide the oil pump drive sprocket gently backwards and forwards to dislodge the inner needle roller bearing. ","Oil pump drive sprocket (engine shown inverted)","Needle roller bearing","Support the oil pump drive sprocket and carefully remove the bearing.","Needle roller bearing (engine shown inverted)","Oil pump drive sprocket","Note the position of the washer under the oil pump fixing for the oil pump dowel for installation.","Release the fixings securing the oil pump. Remove the fixings and collect the washer.","Oil pump","Fixings","Washer","Use a suitable tool to slide the dowel upwards to release the oil pump from the crankcase. It is not necessary to remove the dowel completely from the oil pump.","Oil pump","Dowel","Detach the drive chain from the oil pump.","Oil pump","Drive chain","Carefully withdraw the oil pump from the crankcase.","Remove and discard the O-ring from the inlet sleeve on the coolant pump body."],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType05","createdAt":"2024-04-18T13:08:20.803Z","updatedAt":"2024-04-18T13:08:20.803Z","__v":0}